@startuml
title Medplum Platform Architecture with KHIE Workflow Integration
left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "End users\nclinicians, administrators" as users
actor "External clinical systems\nFHIR, HL7, DICOM, webhooks" as external
actor "On-premise devices\nand source systems" as devices

cloud "Internet / private network" as network

rectangle "Medplum application boundary" {
  component "Web application\nReact static application\nNginx in container deployments" as app
  component "FHIR API server\nNode.js / Express\nFHIR R4 API, authentication,\nresource and binary operations" as server
  component "Bot runtime\nVM-context default in supplied\nlocal configuration\noptional cloud/serverless runtime" as bots
  component "KHIE workflow packages\ncore client + bots + React UI" as khie
  component "Medplum Agent (optional)\nOn-premise connectivity\nHL7/device bridge" as agent
  database "PostgreSQL\nFHIR resources and application data" as postgres
  database "Redis\ncache and background queueing" as redis
  folder "Binary storage\nlocal file or configured object storage" as binary
  component "OpenTelemetry instrumentation" as otel
}

cloud "KHIE APIs\nOAuth token endpoint\nclaims and preauth endpoints" as khieapi
cloud "Observability backend\noperator selected" as observability

users --> network
network --> app : HTTPS browser session
app --> server : FHIR API / OAuth flows
external --> server : configured integration interfaces
devices --> agent : site-local protocols
agent --> server : authenticated agent connection
server --> postgres : persistent FHIR and application data
server --> redis : cache and jobs
server --> binary : Binary resources
server --> bots : bot execution and triggers
app --> khie : reusable workflow components
khie --> bots : execute KHIE workflow bots
bots --> postgres : Claim, Task, Encounter,\nCoverage, Patient updates
bots --> khieapi : authenticated KHIE REST calls
server --> otel : service metrics and traces
otel --> observability : exported telemetry

note bottom of app
The application package is a static React build.
The KHIE UI components are reusable package exports,
not a separate application server.
end note

note bottom of bots
Bot runtime selection is configuration and deployment dependent.
The full-stack Docker example enables VM-context bots.
end note
@enduml